1025AM DIVERSITY RESULTS AND PLOTTING 
* ok diversity done 
* Final diversity model retained overall reef-type trajectories, with pair treated as an adjustment factor.
* Shannon diversity increased significantly through time on both artificial and natural reefs.
* Artificial reefs increased numerically faster, but the temporal slopes did not differ significantly.
* The increase from before to after deployment was significantly greater on artificial reefs.
* Artificial reefs initially had significantly lower diversity than natural reefs, but this difference was smaller and non-significant by the end of the study.
* Pattern suggests possible convergence, although convergence was not statistically supported.